This paper is about off-policy reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper introduces a new method for improving the efficiency of trace utilization in off-policy reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
